---
description: Enforce Input/Output/Must-never contracts on TypeScript and JavaScript files
globs: ["**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}"]
---

## Contract Format — Required

Every new or significantly modified function, component, hook, or module must begin with:

```ts
// Input: what this block receives (props, arguments, store state)
// Output: what this block produces (rendered JSX, return value, side effect)
// Must never: behaviors this block is prohibited from having
```

## Examples

```ts
// Input: userId string from route params
// Output: User object or null
// Must never: modify database, send notifications, or throw unhandled errors

// Input: auth store state via useAuthStore hook
// Output: boolean isAuthenticated + current user object
// Must never: fetch tokens directly, call sign-in methods, or redirect

// Input: array of site objects from API response
// Output: rendered grid of SiteCard components
// Must never: fetch data, filter/sort logic, or manage selection state
```

## Rules

- Write the contract BEFORE the implementation.
- The "Must never" line is a hard constraint, not a suggestion.
- When editing an existing file: update the contract if the behavior changed.
- If you cannot write a one-line "Must never", the block has too many concerns — split it.
